         Example programs for MCC assembler/Lattice-C          ADB 6/2/86
         ============================================          ----------

THIS FILE AND THE FILES INDICATED BELOW (present on this disk) ARE ALL
PUBLIC DOMAIN - PLEASE FEEL FREE TO PASS ON COPIES TO ANYONE. All program
sources are in a form suitable for the Metacomco macro assembler and
Metacomco Lattice-C compiler.

The example program files include :-

Assembler source files...

ANDY.ASM	So I can put my name in perpective (pardon the very bad pun)
BIOSINT.ASM	Installing intercepts in TOS.
COLROT.ASM	Supervisor mode, accessing ST hardware, writing C bindings.
CONINIT.ASM	Example of using the BIOS from assembler. Changing key tables.
GLIB.ASM	More C bindings - a line-A graphics library.
GRAF3D.ASM	A line-A graphics example. Spinning 3D images.
SPRITE.ASM	Using line-A - ST software sprites.
OSLIB.ASM	More C bindings. Just as an example, this is the source
		for the GEMDOS, BIOS & XBIOS functions as implemented
		in the Lattice standard library (CLIB.BIN) on the MCC
		Lattice-C compiler disk.

To assemble, run the assembler with a command line like

SPRITE.ASM TO SPRITE.BIN

this will produce the file SPRITE.BIN which will need to be run through the
linker to produce an executable file.
 
Lattice C source files...

BWDEMO.C	An example C program to use the line-A bindings.
C3D.C		Another line-A example. A version of GRAF3D.ASM for comparison.
COLMROT.C	An example C program using GEM and COLROT (see above).
SPTEST.C	A C version of the assembler SPRITE demo using line-A library.
VDIEX.C		An example of the use of GEM VDI functions.

Assembler object files, ready for linking...

COLROT.BIN	The assembler output for COLROT (above) in GST format.
GLIB.BIN	The assembler output for the line-A 'library' above.

The final program files, ready to run...

